               <head xml:lang="eng">First portion</head>
	
	<p>
		<lb n="1"/>ḻaippaḻam <gap quantity="2" reason="lost" unit="character"></gap>ṉū<gap quantity="3" reason="lost" unit="character"></gap>
		<lb n="2"/>cavarku nellu kala<gap quantity="3" reason="lost" unit="character"></gap>
		<lb n="3"/>mukkuṟuṇiyum palaka<gap quantity="5" reason="lost" unit="character"></gap>
		<lb n="4" break="no"/>yum tayir-amutu paliṅ<gap quantity="5" reason="lost" unit="character"></gap>
		<lb n="5" break="no"/>llu  kalanē tūṇi pa<gap quantity="6" reason="lost" unit="character"></gap>
		<lb n="6" break="no"/>mutu Aṭa viṟakiṭum<gap quantity="6" reason="lost" unit="character"></gap>
		<lb n="7" break="no"/><unclear>m</unclear> Ilai Amutu pā<gap quantity="6" reason="lost" unit="character"></gap>
		<lb n="8"/><unclear>I</unclear>raṇṭu mañcāṭiyum Amutu ceytaruḷi<choice><orig>n</orig><reg>ṉ</reg></choice>a pa–<!--@emfr:these dashes appear from here on. What do they mean? That the gap is unknown?-->
		<lb n="9"/>Āṭiyaruḷa vāḻaippaḻam Aiñcukkup po–
		<lb n="10" break="no"/>yum tiruppukaikku citārikku<unclear>m</unclear> pon Arai māvu–
		<lb n="11" break="no"/>ku<choice><orig>n</orig><reg>ṉ</reg></choice>ṟiyum tiruvōlakkattukku Eriyum tiruviḷak–
		<lb n="12" break="no"/>ṇṇappañ ceyyum paru<hi rend="grantha">ṣai</hi> nāyan
		<lb n="13" break="no"/>kkup pon kaḻañcum <hi rend="grantha">śrī</hi>purāṇam <!--@emfr: the text here is in bold, but don't know why. Maybe just to underline the text?--> vācippān– 
		<lb n="14" break="no"/>ḻañcum Āka pon patin kaḻañcaraiyē I–
		<lb n="15" break="no"/>nūṟṟaṟu kalanē tūṇi Arunāḻi<unclear>yum</unclear><gap quantity="4" reason="lost" unit="character"></gap>
		<lb n="16"/>Ākat tirumañcaṉam Iraṇṭukkum peru–
		<lb n="17" break="no"/>ñcē kālē ku<choice><orig>n</orig><reg>ṉ</reg></choice>ṟiyināl nellu Irunā–
		<lb n="18" break="no"/>nē kuṟuṇikku kiḻakkaṭaiya viṭṭa nilam<gap quantity="1" reason="lost" unit="character"></gap>
		<lb n="19"/><gap quantity="1" reason="lost" unit="character"></gap>l vanta ceṅkaḻunir-t tiruppaḷḷi-t-tāma E–
		<lb n="20" break="no"/>āḻiyāka nāḷ Oṉṟukku nellu Irunā–<!--@emfr:If I just put the first letter of the line ā, is it clear that it belongs to the previous lost consonant or shall I add that the consonant is no longer legible? I did the second...-->
		<lb n="21"/>nellu Irunūṟṟōrupattaṟu kalamu–
		<lb n="22" break="no"/>ṟṟu nāṟppattaṟu kalattukku kiḻa–
		<lb n="23" break="no"/>ku viṭṭa nilam–
		<lb n="24" break="no"/>yi<hi rend="grantha">ṣṇa</hi>va<hi rend="grantha"><hi rend="grantha">r</hi></hi><gap quantity="1" reason="lost" unit="character"></gap><hi rend="grantha">ai</hi>–
	</p>
            </div>
	
	<div type="textpart" n="B" xml:lang="tam-Latn">
